<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idbddf1dd3-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s6956"><num value="6956">§ 6956.</num><heading> Authorization of appropriations</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There are authorized to be appropriated to the Secretary of Commerce $5,000,000 for each of fiscal years 1980, 1981, and 1982 and $1,500,000 for each of the fiscal years 1985 through 1988 to carry out the purposes of this subchapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idbddf1dd4-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/89/272/tII/s5006">Pub. L. 89–272, title II, § 5006</ref>, as added <ref href="/us/pl/96/482/s31/f/1">Pub. L. 96–482, § 31(f)(1)</ref>, <date date="1980-10-21">Oct. 21, 1980</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/94/2353">94 Stat. 2353</ref>; amended <ref href="/us/pl/98/616/s2/h">Pub. L. 98–616, § 2(h)</ref>, <date date="1984-11-08">Nov. 8, 1984</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/98/3223">98 Stat. 3223</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idbddf1dd5-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idbddf1dd6-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="idbddf1dd7-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1984—<ref href="/us/pl/98/616">Pub. L. 98–616</ref> authorized appropriation of $1,500,000 for each of fiscal years 1985 through 1988.</p>
</note>
